OL,3,CScottish and Irish rocks may be rare
OL,4,Crecord of 'snowball Earth', study
OL,5,Csuggests
OL,7,FA rock formation that spans Ireland
OL,8,Fand Scotland may be a rare record of
OL,9,Fsnowball Earth ` a crucial moment in
OL,10,Fplanetary history when the globe was
OL,11,Fcovered in ice.
OL,13,FThe Port Askaig Formation, which is
OL,14,Fmade up of layers of rock up to 1.1km
OL,15,Fthick, was likely to have been laid
OL,16,Fdown between 662 and 720 million years
OL,17,Fago during the Sturtian glaciation,
OL,18,Fresearch suggests.
