OL,3,CScottish and Irish rocks may be rare
OL,4,Crecord of 'snowball Earth', study
OL,5,Csuggests
OL,7,FThis was the first of two global
OL,8,Ffreezes thought to have triggered the
OL,9,Fdevelopment of complex life.
OL,11,FAccording to the new study, one
OL,12,Fsection of exposed rock, found on
OL,13,FScottish islands called the
OL,14,FGarvellachs, is unique as it shows the
OL,15,Ftransition into snowball Earth from a
OL,16,Fpreviously warm, tropical environment.
OL,18,FOther rocks that formed at a similar
OL,19,Ftime, like some in North America and
OL,20,FNamibia, are missing this transition.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
