OL,3,CScottish and Irish rocks may be rare
OL,4,Crecord of 'snowball Earth', study
OL,5,Csuggests
OL,7,FTherefore researchers believe their
OL,8,Ffindings may be the world's most
OL,9,Fcomplete record of snowball Earth ` a
OL,10,Ftheory that suggests Earth's oceans
OL,11,Fand land surfaces were covered by ice
OL,12,Ffrom the poles to the Equator during
OL,13,Fat least two extreme cooling events
OL,14,Fbetween 2.4 billion and 580 million
OL,15,Fyears ago.
OL,17,FSenior author Professor Graham
OL,18,FShields, of University College London
OL,19,F(UCL) Earth Sciences, said: "These
OL,20,Frocks record a time when Earth was
OL,21,Fcovered in ice.
