OL,3,CScottish and Irish rocks may be rare
OL,4,Crecord of 'snowball Earth', study
OL,5,Csuggests
OL,7,FHe explained that most areas of the
OL,8,Fworld are missing the layers in the
OL,9,Frocks that record a tropical
OL,10,Fenvironment and mark the transition,
OL,11,Fbecause the ancient glaciers scraped
OL,12,Fand eroded away the rocks underneath.
OL,14,F"But in Scotland by some miracle the
OL,15,Ftransition can be seen," Mr Rugen said.
OL,17,FLasting some 60 million years, the
OL,18,FSturtian glaciation was one of two big
OL,19,Ffreezes that occurred during the
OL,20,FCryogenian Period ` between 635 and
OL,21,F720 million years ago.
