OL,3,CScottish and Irish rocks may be rare
OL,4,Crecord of 'snowball Earth', study
OL,5,Csuggests
OL,7,FFor billions of years before this,
OL,8,Flife consisted only of single-celled
OL,9,Forganisms and algae.
OL,11,FAfter this period, complex life
OL,12,Fquickly emerged, with most animals
OL,13,Ftoday similar in fundamental ways to
OL,14,Fthe types of life forms that evolved
OL,15,Fmore than 500 million years ago.
OL,17,FOne theory is that the hostile nature
OL,18,Fof the extreme cold may have prompted
OL,19,Fsingle-celled organisms to co-operate
OL,20,Fwith each other, forming multicellular
OL,21,Flife.
