OL,4,Crecord of 'snowball Earth', study
OL,5,Csuggests
OL,7,FThe advance and retreat of the ice
OL,8,Facross the planet was thought to have
OL,9,Fhappened relatively quickly, over
OL,10,Fthousands of years, because of the
OL,11,Falbedo effect ` that is, the more ice
OL,12,Fthere is, the more sunlight is
OL,13,Freflected back into space, and vice
OL,14,Fversa.
OL,16,FProf Shields explained: "The retreat
OL,17,Fof the ice would have been
OL,18,Fcatastrophic. Life had been used to
OL,19,Ftens of millions of years of deep
OL,20,Ffreeze.
