OL,5,Csuggests
OL,7,FThe researchers said the new age
OL,8,Fconstraints for the rocks may provide
OL,9,Fthe evidence needed for the site to be
OL,10,Fdeclared as a marker for the start of
OL,11,Fthe Cryogenian Period.
OL,13,FThis marker, known as a Global
OL,14,FBoundary Stratotype Section and Point
OL,15,F(GSSP), is sometimes referred to as a
OL,16,Fgolden spike, as a gold spike is
OL,17,Fdriven into the rock to mark the
OL,18,Fboundary, and these sites attract
OL,19,Fvisitors from around the world.
